 <body>   
    <h1> Arroz Caldo </h1>
    <img src="https://i0.wp.com/thenotsocreativecook.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Arroz-Caldo-4.jpg?fit=1725%2C1142&ssl=1" alt="finished Arroz Caldo">
    <p><h3> Description</h3></p>
    <p><h5> Arroz Caldo is one of my favorite childhood recipes. It is <strong>THE</strong> ideal meal for a cold or rainy day, as it will warm you up and change the mood almost insantly </h5></p>
    <p><h3>Ingredients:</h3></p>
    <ul>
        <l>2 cups of white rice</l>
        <l>1/2 lb of chicken legs</l>
        <l>5 cups of water</l>
        <l>3 tbsp of ginger</l>
        <l>4 tbsp of garlic</l>
        <l>2 tbsp of olive oil</l>
        <l>1 tsp of black pepper</l>
        <l>1 tbsp of fish sauce</l>
        <l>1/4 cup of green onions</l>
        <l>1 dozen eggs</l>
        <l>calamansi (or lemon)</l>
    </ul>
    <p><h3>Steps</h3></p>
    <ol>
        <l>In a large pot, add olive oil, chopped ginger and 2 tbsp of chopped garlic</l>
        <l>Once ginger and garlic have browned, add in chicken legs. Cook thoroughly and wait till chicken is brown</l>
        <l>Add water to pot and allow to boil</l>
        <l>Once water is boiling, add rice, black pepper, and fish sauce, and stir</l>
        <l>Allow to cook for 15 minutes or until rice is soft</l>
        <l>In another pan, add olive oil. Once hot, add shopped garlic. Cook till crisped but not burnt</l>
        <l>Scoop desired amount into bowl, and add chopped green onions, fried garlic, and sliced eggs as toppings</l>
        <l>Squeeze 1/4 of calamansi and add fish sauce</l>

    </ol>

</body>
